==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mugwump
<hw>mug"wump`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Algonquin
<ets>mugquomp</ets> a chief.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bolter from the
Republican party in the national election of 1884; an Independent.</def>
<mark>[Political Cant, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who is undecided about an issue, especially
a political one; a person who takes a neutral stance on an issue; a
fence-sitter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mugwumpism</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Mugwumpery</ent>⟦br⟧
